TypeScript strict mode, ESM. All imports use `.js` extensions (Node16 module resolution).

Early returns, small functions (<50 lines), descriptive names. Prefer editing existing files.

Core flow: Traces → NormalizedConversation → Evaluate (metrics + policies) → Diagnose → Report.

Key files:
- src/ingestion/types.ts — NormalizedConversation (universal trace format)
- src/evaluation/types.ts — Report, PolicyResult, Diagnosis, MetricScores
- src/llm/client.ts — createLlmClient() for OpenAI/Anthropic
- src/llm/prompts.ts — all prompt templates (structured JSON output)
- src/llm/json.ts — safeJSONParse() for LLM responses (never raw JSON.parse)
- src/report/generator.ts — buildHtml(report) entry point
- src/report/sections.ts — all report render functions
- src/report/styles.ts — inline CSS, JS, and SVG icons
- src/mcp/tools-read.ts — zero-cost MCP tools
- src/mcp/tools-eval.ts — LLM-cost MCP tools

Tests: vitest, mirror src/ structure, mock LLM responses. Run: npm test
Type-check: npm run lint
Commits: feat: | fix: | test: | docs: | refactor:
